OL,7,F"Prisons are very, very close to full
OL,8,Fand filling up day in day out. The
OL,9,Fworst possible thing would be for the
OL,10,Fsystem to block, because the system
OL,11,Fblocks in prisons if they get
OL,12,Fcompletely full. That kicks back into
OL,13,Fthe courts and into what we do. And
OL,14,Fthat's really dangerous for the public.
OL,16,F"So the government are forced into
OL,17,Fmaking a rapid decision to avoid that
OL,18,Frisk. So it's going to be the least
OL,19,Fworst option they're going to have to
OL,20,Ffind, so I understand what they're
OL,21,Ftrying to do, however not ideal it is."
